data.reddit: I’m a 16 year old female who is 5 foot 4 inches, and weighs 138 pounds, I don’t smoke, I’m not on any medications, and I don’t have any major physical medical issues now, and I haven’t had any problems in the past either. I’m from Saint Louis, Missouri. I have suffered from episodes of depersonalization and derealization since I was about 7 or 8, really as long as I was mentally capable of recognizing that I was in a different dreamlike state. I am now almost 16 and my depersonalization has gotten much worse through middle school, and through my freshman year of high school I was almost constantly dissociating, and I did some research and came to the conclusion that I had DDD (depersonalization derealization disorder), but then I spoke to a cousin who has experienced the same thing, and who also has severe depression, and she said her depersonalization was just a symptom of her depression, and it improved a lot once her depression was treated. My problem is, I don’t think I was depressed at 7, so I don’t think depression was the cause of my dissociation then. By 7th and 8th grade I certainly was depressed, and beyond that for sure. So now I’m not sure if I have DDD or if it’s just depression. Any insights on this situation would be greatly appreciated. Thank you
